\begin_layout Paragraph
Limitations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So far only the colors which are specified in the code can be detected by the robot. This limits the interaction possiblities. A more interactive approach would be that any color could be said or that the words can be specified by the person interacting with the robot, e.g. via speech input. But permitting the robot to detect more colors is difficult, as colors appear quite different in changing light conditions. Distinguishing black, red, blue and green is easier as the RGB values are very different.
\end_layout

